    "_postman_id": "cms-auth-api-collection",
    "name": "CMS - Authentication API",
    "description": "Authentication API collection for the Clinic Management System with Clean Architecture.\n\n## üîê Authentication API (/api/auth)\n\nThis collection focuses specifically on authentication and authorization endpoints:\n\n- **User Registration**: Create new user accounts with role-based access (admin, doctor, receptionist)\n- **User Login**: Authenticate users with email/username support\n- **JWT Token Management**: Token generation, validation and refresh\n- **Password Validation**: Password strength validation and requirements\n- **Doctor Registration**: Doctor-specific profile fields during registration\n- **Role-Based Access**: Different registration flows based on user roles\n\n## Testing Coverage\n\n- ‚úÖ User registration (all roles)\n- ‚úÖ Login with email and username\n- ‚úÖ JWT token validation\n- ‚úÖ Password strength testing\n- ‚úÖ Error handling (invalid credentials, validation errors)\n- ‚úÖ Doctor-specific registration fields\n- ‚úÖ Authentication middleware testing\n\n## Environment Variables\n\nThis collection uses the following environment variables:\n- `cms_local`: http://localhost:4000 (for local development)\n- `cms_prod`: https://capstone-api.up.railway.app (for production)\n- `baseUrl`: Base URL for API endpoints\n- `authToken`: JWT token for authenticated requests\n- Various test data variables for dynamic testing",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "version": {
      "major": 2,
      "minor": 3,
      "patch": 0
    }
  },
